07_read_histogram


  1. Question

    S-ID.A: Summarize, represent, and interpret data on a single count or measurement variable. Use calculators, spreadsheets, and other technology as appropriate.

    A spinner was made to model a continuous triangular distribution. It was spun 50 times; those locations are marked.


    The name “triangular distribution” comes from the probability density curve.


    Notice that because the spinner is continuous, it generates data like 321.729947 and 325.0745512. Of course, a human would probably round to the nearest tenth or so.

    Actual question

    The 50 spins were used to generate a histogram.


    • How many spins were less than 316?
      • \(\#(x<316) =\)
    • What proportion of spins were less than 316?
      • \(\mathrm{proportion}(x<316) =\)
    • How many spins were more than 318?
      • \(\#(x>318) =\)
    • What proportion of spins were more than 318?
      • \(\mathrm{proportion}(x>318) =\)
    • How many spins were between 314 and 326?
      • \(\#(314<x<326) =\)
    • What proportion of spins were between 314 and 326?
      • \(\mathrm{proportion}(314<x<326) =\)


    Solution

    • \(\#(x<316) =\) 13
    • \(\mathrm{proportion}(x<316) = \frac{13}{50} =\) 0.26
    • \(\#(x>318) =\) 26
    • \(\mathrm{proportion}(x>318) = \frac{26}{50} =\) 0.52
    • \(\#(314<x<326) =\) 36
    • \(\mathrm{proportion}(314<x<326) = \frac{36}{50} =\) 0.72

    You might find the following visualizations helpful.


    \[3+7+3=13\]


    \[3+8+7+4+1+2+1+0=26\]


    \[3+11+3+8+7+4=36\]
